    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-08T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_BJW1" type="from">Ballantine</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-08T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 8, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 10—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am reliably informed that yesterday <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_HH2">Hu
                        Han-min</persName>, <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WCC1">C. C.
                        Wu</persName> and Li Tsung-jen sent a joint telegram to <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_WC1">Wang Ching-wei</persName> from Hong Kong lauding
                    his action in resigning and urging him to proceed there. <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_CC6">Chen Chi-tang</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_SFK1">Sun Fo</persName> separately took similar
                    action today. It is believed in political circles here that <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_CK3">Chiang</persName> will be unable to maintain his
                    prestige without <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WC1">Wang</persName>’s
                    support, and that if the latter complies with the invitation of the southern
                    leaders there will be far-reaching political consequences.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Department, Legation and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ballantine</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
